<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO MISSES GOAL OF UNIVERSAL VACCINATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The World Health Organization has failed in its bid to vaccinate every child in 
the world against polio, measles and other childhood diseases by the end of the 
year, a leading French researcher says. Marc Girard of the Pasteur Institute 
says one-third of the world's children still have not been vaccinated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
