<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAIWAN REPATRIATES 71 STOWAWAYS TO CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAIPEI, Taiwan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan's Red Cross repatriated 71 stowaways to China on Friday and officials 
promised there would be additional transfers until all illegal Chinese in 
detention have been sent home. 
</P>
<P>
"We hope that all can be sent back, and will repatriate both new arrivals and 
those already here as quickly as possible," Red Cross Deputy Secretary-General 
Chang Sung-mo said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
