<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC IRVINE BEATEN IN CHATTANOOGA FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith Nelson scored 32 points, including 15 in the final nine minutes, as 
Tennessee Chattanooga rallied to beat UC Irvine, 88-68, Saturday night in the 
championship game of the Tennessee Chattanooga tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine (5-7) closed to within 60-58 on Craig Marshall's layup with 9:00 to 
play. 
</P>
<P>
But Nelson and Derrick Kirce, who scored eight of his 15 points in the final 
nine minutes, keyed a run as Tennessee Chattanooga (6-5) of the Southern 
Conference outscored the Anteaters, 28-10. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine led most of the first half while making seven of 13 three-point shots 
before Nelson hit a free throw to key the Moccasins' comeback for a 43-40 lead 
with 1:14 left. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine tied the game, 43-43, at halftime, but went cold from three-point range 
and made one of 10 attempts in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Herdman led Irvine with 16 points. Cornelius Banks had 12 points and Dylan 
Rigdon 11. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's next game will be Wednesday at Utah State. The Anteaters then play at 
San Jose State in their Big West Conference opener next Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
