<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SAN MARINO; 
</P>
<P>
TREE RECYCLING PLAN SET UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the first time, the city will recycle residents' Christmas trees. 
</P>
<P>
"For San Marino, this is a start," said Keith Till, acting city manager. "Every 
little bit helps." 
</P>
<P>
Residents can take trees to Lacy Park from 9 a.m. to noon on Thursday. Workers 
will run the trees through a "chipper," grinding them into recyclable material. 
</P>
<P>
The service is part of the community's new comprehensive recycling program. 
Residents, who may be asked to show driver's licenses, are asked to remove 
nails or other protrusions from trees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
