<HEADLINE>
<P>
SYMPATHY, AID FOR THE HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have heard people say that they don't give money to homeless people because 
they'll just spend it on alcohol or drugs. What I do to get around this is to 
give fast-food gift certificates to street people who ask me for change. 
</P>
<P>
The fact that those I give them to are almost always happy to get them 
demonstrates that these people don't just want to get high. 
</P>
<P>
TOM SINSKY, Hollywood 
</P>
