SHEVARDNADZE'S RESIGNATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times presented verbatim highlights of Shevardnadze's speech in which he 
clearly states that he is still a Communist (Part A, Dec. 21). Anyone who ever 
studied Communism must know that it is a doctrine that advocates the 
dictatorship of the proletariat. So, how can Shevardnadze resign his post 
