<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAIT IN LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In your "Anti-Immigrant Sentiment Protested" article of Dec. 10, you only once 
stated that the two major groups trying to bring the border problem to 
attention in Washington, D.C., are concerned about "illegal immigration," not 
those who do the paperwork and wait in line like other honest citizens of all 
nations of the world. 
</P>
<P>
I give "open arms" to any immigrant who enters this country through the border 
checkpoints for people, autos, aircraft or ships. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone entering this country illegally, I support giving the chance to plead 
his or her case to the government as to why he or she had to enter the country 
illegally. 
</P>
<P>
But I also support the right of this nation to throw out all those who fail to 
register with the U.S. government after they enter illegally or after a hearing 
are found without a defense in why they should be allowed to stay in this 
country when millions of other honest citizens of all nations of the world wait 
in line. 
</P>
<P>
LT. I.G. BEALL JR., La Jolla 
</P>
</TEXT>
