<HEADLINE>
<P>
CENTURY TOURNAMENT; 
</P>
<P>
EL MODENA'S SECOND WIND BEATS BUENA PARK FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With six minutes remaining and Buena Park leading by 10 points, El Modena's 
struggling offense got a second wind Saturday night in the championship game of 
the Carl's Jr. Century Basketball Tournament at Century High School. 
</P>
<P>
El Modena found new life when Buena Park began to commit a rash of turnovers 
that allowed the Vanguards to tie the score at the end of regulation and beat 
the Coyotes, 52-46, in overtime for the tournament title. 
</P>
<P>
"We picked up defensively and did some things really different offensively," El 
Modena Coach Tim Tivenan said. "Buena Park shut off our passing lanes really 
well and stopped us most of the game, so we started doing more screening and 
setting things up a little better." 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park (8-5) led the entire game behind center Richard Harvey, who finished 
with 23 points on 11 of 14 shooting, and with help from guards Prentice Johnson 
and Chris Stone, who plugged up the Vanguard offense. 
</P>
<P>
As the Coyotes led, 39-29, El Modena (9-5) started capitalizing on the Coyotes' 
fourth-quarter turnovers and trailed, 44-42, after Bob Baytosh's three-point 
basket with 36 seconds remaining. After another Buena Park turnover, Mike 
Terry's eight-foot baseline jumper at 1:01 tied the score, 44-44, to send the 
game into overtime. 
</P>
<P>
Terry hit the first basket with 1:20 remaining in overtime and added a pair of 
free throws with 38 seconds left for a 50-46 lead. Terry was named MVP for the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 80, Loara 67 -- Fullerton (7-6) relied on balanced scoring to offset 
the firepower of Loara's Tes Whitlock to capture the third-place title. Pete 
Quis scored 17 points and Craig Olsen and Chris Hartshorn had 16 points each 
for the Indian. Whitlock scored 27 points. 
</P>
<P>
St. Paul 58, Westminster 52 -- Greg Gomez and Brandon Ertle scored 16 points 
each to lead the Swordsmen (4-7) over the Lions, who were led by Jesse Gomez 
(15) in the consolation championship game. 
</P>
<P>
Century 66, Newport Harbor 64 -- The host Centurions (7-4) upset the Sailors 
with 27-point burst in the fourth quarter. Sophomore Darvin Thompson led 
Century with 30 points. Huy Nguyen and Justin McIntee led the Sailors (8-6) 
with 35 and 21 points respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
