<TEXT>
<P>
Brunell Mori scored 19 points, including 17 in the second half, as Grant High 
defeated Kennedy, 65-56, Saturday night for the championship of the Birmingham 
tournament. Mori was named tournament most valuable player. 
</P>
<P>
Grant made four three-point baskets in the first quarter and six in the first 
half to take a 30-22 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
University 70, Taft 69 -- Ken Thames scored with 30 seconds left in overtime 
for University for the championship of the Eagle Rock tournament. 
</P>
<P>
