<P>
CHAS'WHIM'S VICTORY AT LAUREL IS OUT OF SIGHT TO HIS BACKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAUREL, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In fog so thick racegoers couldn't see the horses they had bet on, Chas'Whim 
captured the $100,000 Congressional Handicap at the Laurel Race Course on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Chas'Whim, who carried top weight of 119 pounds in the field of seven, 
completed 1 1/4 miles in 2:01 4-5 over a muddy track. 
</P>
<P>
Jet Stream finished a 1 3/4 lengths back in second place and Reputed Testamony 
was another three-quarters of a length behind in third. 
</P>
