HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
MERCHANTS DONATE TO POLICE BIKE PATROL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fledgling police bike patrol program in Hollywood has received a boost from 
local merchants and property owners, who have contributed more than $17,000 to 
the program. 
</P>
<P>
The contributions, raised at a December fund-raiser, will go toward buying 
bikes, outfits and other gear for the Los Angeles Police Department's Hollywood 
Division bike patrol unit. 
</P>
<P>
The donations will provide funds for at least 14 members of the unit to pedal 
on and around Hollywood Boulevard at least five nights a week, according to 
Nina Greenberg, a consultant to area merchants. 
</P>
<P>
A similar program is under way in West Hollywood and other parts of the 
Westside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
