<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. government announced it is seeking the extradition of the mayor of 
Zacapa, Guatemala, and two other men arrested in Guatemala's largest cocaine 
seizure. Police on Thursday arrested Mayor Arnoldo Vargas Estrada, 52, Otto 
Evelio Quiro Davila, 34, and Victor Enrique Escobar Arias, 37, and seized 5,000 
pounds of cocaine. The U.S. Embassy in Guatemala City said the Justice 
Department wants to prosecute the three on charges of smuggling and 
distributing drugs in the United States. 
