<HEADLINE>
<P>
SILENCE BROKEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As one of the many thousands of hearing-impaired people who are totally 
dependent on closed captioned TV for "hearing" programs, may I offer my 
congratulations to the broadcasters who offer "Arsenio Hall" (KCOP, weeknights) 
as captioned. Also to the TNT Network, which is captioning its new movies. It 
is such a pleasure to be able to participate in watching and understanding what 
is happening. 
</P>
<P>
Eila Henriksen, Ojai 
</P>
</TEXT>
